The paper proposes a new method for open-world learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The method is based on meta-learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. The application of the method is product classification, which involves computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
